{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place sumac, oregano, salt and pepper into a small bowl and stir to combine. Set aside.","Place water, carrot, onion, celery and garlic into mixing bowl. Place Varoma into position and weigh beef into it, ensuring that lid will close securely. Rub reserved spice mix all over meat, then secure Varoma lid and steam <nobr>60 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Remove Varoma lid, weigh potatoes into Varoma dish around roast, secure Varoma lid and steam <nobr>30 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Meanwhile, line a baking tray with baking paper and set aside.","Preheat oven to 220°C. Carefully remove potatoes and place onto prepared baking tray. Roughly squash potatoes with the back of a fork, drizzle with oil and season with salt and pepper. Bake for 20-25 minutes (220°C) or until dry and crispy. Meanwhile, continue cooking beef roast.","Secure Varoma lid and steam <nobr>30-45 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr> or until beef is cooked to your liking.","Set Varoma aside and allow beef to rest. Blend gravy in mixing bowl <nobr>1 min\/speed 4<\/nobr><strong>-6, increasing speed gradually from speed 4 to speed 6<\/strong>. Transfer gravy into a jug and set aside. Transfer potatoes into a serving bowl with parsley, olives and extra oil, then season with salt and pepper. Gently toss to combine. Slice beef and serve with smashed potatoes, gravy and salad greens."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["1 - 2 tbsp sumac, to taste","1 tbsp dried oregano","1 ½ tsp salt, plus extra for seasoning","1 tsp ground black pepper, plus extra for seasoning","1600 g water","1 carrot, cut into pieces","1 brown onion, cut into quarters","3 celery stalks, cut into pieces","3 garlic cloves, roughly chopped","1200 - 1300 g beef roast, trimmed (see Tip)","1000 g new baby potatoes, washed","1 - 2 tbsp oil, plus extra to taste","1 - 2 sprigs fresh flat-leaf parsley, roughly chopped","2 - 3 tbsp pitted black olives, roughly chopped","mixed leafy greens, of choice to serve"]}],"id":"r252395","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-bvJK_PKsx8M\/XZQGT9eckSI\/AAAAAAAAb8o\/IYCXmODnDLYnXxuhFp2yhnIB5GwT6uOUgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_MsuR33AyR4Z1bshk.png","title":"Sumac beef with olive and parsley smashed potatoes","publishedAt":"2018-07-30T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"52.9 g","fat":"17.2 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"24.2 g","calories":"1998.1 kJ \/ 475.7 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking tray, baking paper, jug, serving bowl, small bowl, fork, oven","hintsAndTricks":["You can use either a topside roast or a bolar blade roast in this recipe; choose the one that best fits within your budget. Ensure the roast fits comfortably in the Varoma dish and the lid closes securely - you may need to trim the roast for it to fit."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","2h 30m","6 portions"]}